        int getTimeStep(java.util.GregorianCalendar date)
        Gets the timestep that corresponds to the specified GregorianCalendar date. If no such timestep is found then return Axes.TIME_STEP_NOT_FOUND.
        Parameters:
        date - the GregorianCalendar date whose time step we want
        Returns:
        the timestep that corresponds to the specified date. If no such timestep is found then return Axes.TIME_STEP_NOT_FOUND.
